This is README file for Algorithm PA#1
Author: 項達均 b11901040
Date: 2024/3/18
=====
SYNOPSIS:

NTU_sort -[IS|MS|QS|RQS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>

This program supports three different sorting methods: insertion sort, merge sort and heap sort.
=====
DIRECTORY:

bin/	  executable binary
doc/	  reports
inputs/   input data (unsorted)
outputs/  output result (sorted)
lib/	  library
src/ 	  source C++ codes
utility/  checker
======
HOW TO COMPILE:

Then compile the demo, simply follow the following steps
	make
======
HOW TO RUN:

	cd bin/
	./bin/NTU_sort -[IS|MS|QS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>
	For example,
	under <student_id>_pa1
	./bin/NTU_sort -MS inputs/1000.case1.in outputs/1000.case1.out
======
HOW TO VERIFY RESULT

    cd utility/
    ./PA1_Result_Checker <input_file_name> <output_file_name>
	For example,
	under <student_id>_pa1
	./utility/PA1_Result_Checker inputs/1000.case1.in outputs/1000.case1.out

OTHER NOTICE:
